title: 500 Chances
description:
Written for the square “Death.”

Losing Tony devastates Stephen. He casts a spell on himself, hoping to get over Tony’s death by creating alternate lifetimes in his head, in which he loses Tony in many different ways.

500 lifetimes later, Stephen finally admits that the spell isn’t working as intended.

title: Dream Guy
description:
Written for the square “Fantasy.”

At a party, 29-year-old Tony Stark named his dream guy. Other people at the party did, too. Then a bet was made: whoever provided photo evidence of having slept with their dream person first would win 10 million dollars.

Two decades later, Tony Stark would win that bet.

summary: Bleeding Edge armor was Iron Man's most powerful suit, yet he couldn't defeat Thanos. Why? It regenerates and creates any...
question: Bleeding Edge armor was Iron Man's most powerful suit, yet he couldn't defeat Thanos. Why? It regenerates and creates any weapon.
answer:
Currently it is the most powerful suit, but alas, it was still not enough. If Tony fully intends to create another suit of armor, he’ll need something stronger. I doubt Vibranium will do the trick, possibly something from Eitri. Eitri and the dwarves are known for creating powerful weapons, including the Infinity Gauntlet and Mjonir. 

Maybe, Tony with the help of Thor and Nebula shall create a powerful suit armor made from the same material of those two weapons. Or…perhaps the material Odin used to create the Destroyer. There are lot of options for Stark if he is willing to keep fighting and defeat Thanos.
